  "format": "tiptap/v1",
  "doc": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Portkey is an LLM gateway that emphasizes observability and intelligent routing. Like LiteLLM, it exposes an OpenAI-compatible API and routes to multiple providers \u2014 but its primary differentiator is a rich, purpose-built dashboard for tracking LLM-specific metrics: latency distributions by model, token cost per user, request traces with prompt/response pairs, and feedback scores linked to individual completions. It is available as a managed cloud service or self-hosted."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "Portkey gateway: observability and routing to Anthropic, Bedrock, and other providers"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Installation and First Request"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "bash"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "pip install portkey-ai\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from portkey_ai import Portkey\n\n# Managed cloud (api.portkey.ai)\nclient = Portkey(\n    api_key=\"pk-live-...\",           # your Portkey API key\n    virtual_key=\"anthropic-vk-...\",  # maps to your stored Anthropic key\n)\n\nresponse = client.chat.completions.create(\n    model=\"claude-opus-4-8\",\n    max_tokens=512,\n    messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"Explain microservice patterns.\"}],\n)\nprint(response.choices[0].message.content)\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "virtual_key",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " stores your actual Anthropic API key in Portkey's vault. Clients never see the real key, and you rotate it in the Portkey dashboard without touching application code."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Using the OpenAI SDK With Portkey"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Portkey is OpenAI SDK-compatible. Route any OpenAI SDK call through Portkey by overriding the base URL and passing Portkey headers:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from openai import OpenAI\nfrom portkey_ai import PORTKEY_GATEWAY_URL, createHeaders\n\nclient = OpenAI(\n    base_url=PORTKEY_GATEWAY_URL,\n    default_headers=createHeaders(\n        api_key=\"pk-live-...\",\n        virtual_key=\"anthropic-vk-...\",\n    ),\n)\n\nresponse = client.chat.completions.create(\n    model=\"claude-opus-4-8\",\n    max_tokens=512,\n    messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"What is a monad?\"}],\n)\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Observability: What Gets Tracked"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Every request through Portkey is automatically logged with:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Full request and response",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": ": System prompt, messages, completion text, finish reason."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Latency breakdown",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": ": TTFT (time-to-first-token) and total response time."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Token usage",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": ": Input, output, and cached tokens with cost estimation."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Model and provider",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": ": Which model served the request and from which provider endpoint."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Metadata",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": ": Custom tags (user ID, session ID, feature name) you attach per request."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Error details",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": ": Status code, provider error type, retry count."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Attach metadata to any request for downstream filtering and attribution:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from portkey_ai import Portkey\n\nclient = Portkey(\n    api_key=\"pk-live-...\",\n    virtual_key=\"anthropic-vk-...\",\n    metadata={\n        \"_user\":    \"user-abc123\",    # correlate logs to a user\n        \"feature\":  \"doc-summarize\",  # cost attribution by feature\n        \"env\":      \"production\",\n    },\n)\n\nresponse = client.chat.completions.create(\n    model=\"claude-sonnet-4-6\",\n    max_tokens=256,\n    messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"Summarize this document: ...\"}],\n)\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Feedback Scores"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Link user feedback to specific completions using the request's trace ID. Portkey correlates feedback scores with model version, prompt, and latency in the dashboard:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import portkey_ai\n\nresponse = client.chat.completions.create(\n    model=\"claude-sonnet-4-6\",\n    max_tokens=256,\n    messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"Write a haiku about databases.\"}],\n)\n\ntrace_id = response.id  # Portkey logs this as the trace identifier\n\n# After the user rates the response (thumbs up = 1, thumbs down = 0)\ndef record_feedback(trace_id: str, score: float, user_id: str) -> None:\n    portkey_ai.feedback.create(\n        trace_id=trace_id,\n        value=score,\n        weight=1,\n        metadata={\"user_id\": user_id},\n    )\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Routing: Fallbacks"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Portkey configs define routing strategies as JSON objects passed at request time. A fallback config tries providers in order until one succeeds:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import json\nfrom portkey_ai import Portkey, createHeaders\nfrom openai import OpenAI\n\n# Fallback config: try Anthropic direct, then Bedrock\nfallback_config = {\n    \"strategy\": {\"mode\": \"fallback\"},\n    \"targets\": [\n        {\n            \"virtual_key\": \"anthropic-vk-primary\",\n            \"override_params\": {\"model\": \"claude-opus-4-8\"},\n        },\n        {\n            \"virtual_key\": \"bedrock-vk-fallback\",\n            \"override_params\": {\"model\": \"anthropic.claude-opus-4-8\"},\n        },\n    ],\n}\n\nclient = OpenAI(\n    base_url=\"https://api.portkey.ai/v1\",\n    default_headers=createHeaders(\n        api_key=\"pk-live-...\",\n        config=json.dumps(fallback_config),\n    ),\n)\n\n# Portkey routes to Anthropic first; on failure, retries on Bedrock\nresponse = client.chat.completions.create(\n    model=\"claude-opus-4-8\",\n    max_tokens=512,\n    messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"Hello\"}],\n)\nprint(f\"Provider used: {response.model}\")\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Routing: Load Balancing"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Distribute traffic across providers using weighted load balancing. Useful for combining Anthropic direct API (primary) with Bedrock (overflow) to stay within rate limits:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "loadbalance_config = {\n    \"strategy\": {\"mode\": \"loadbalance\"},\n    \"targets\": [\n        {\n            \"virtual_key\": \"anthropic-vk-direct\",\n            \"weight\": 70,  # 70% of traffic\n        },\n        {\n            \"virtual_key\": \"bedrock-vk\",\n            \"weight\": 30,  # 30% of traffic\n        },\n    ],\n}\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Routing: Conditional Routing"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Route different request types to different models based on metadata. Send premium users to Opus and standard users to Haiku:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# Set up two clients for different tiers\nopus_client = Portkey(\n    api_key=\"pk-live-...\",\n    virtual_key=\"anthropic-vk-opus\",\n)\n\nhaiku_client = Portkey(\n    api_key=\"pk-live-...\",\n    virtual_key=\"anthropic-vk-haiku\",\n    metadata={\"tier\": \"standard\"},\n)\n\ndef get_client(user_tier: str) -> Portkey:\n    return opus_client if user_tier == \"premium\" else haiku_client\n\ndef complete(prompt: str, user_tier: str, user_id: str) -> str:\n    c = get_client(user_tier)\n    # Add per-request metadata for tracing\n    resp = c.with_options(metadata={\"_user\": user_id}).chat.completions.create(\n        model=\"claude-opus-4-8\" if user_tier == \"premium\" else \"claude-haiku-4-5\",\n        max_tokens=512,\n        messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": prompt}],\n    )\n    return resp.choices[0].message.content\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Semantic Caching"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Portkey's semantic cache stores responses and returns cached results for semantically similar queries \u2014 not just byte-exact repeats. Enable it in the config:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "cache_config = {\n    \"cache\": {\"mode\": \"semantic\", \"max_age\": 3600},  # 1-hour TTL\n    \"targets\": [{\"virtual_key\": \"anthropic-vk-...\"}],\n}\n\nclient = OpenAI(\n    base_url=\"https://api.portkey.ai/v1\",\n    default_headers=createHeaders(\n        api_key=\"pk-live-...\",\n        config=json.dumps(cache_config),\n    ),\n)\n\n# \"What is machine learning?\" and \"Explain machine learning\" may hit the same cache entry\nresponse = client.chat.completions.create(\n    model=\"claude-haiku-4-5\",\n    max_tokens=256,\n    messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"What is machine learning?\"}],\n)\n# Check if served from cache\ncache_status = response.model_extra.get(\"portkey_cache_status\")  # \"HIT\" or \"MISS\"\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "blockquote",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Semantic cache tradeoff: ",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "bold"
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Semantic caching introduces a vector similarity lookup on every request. For short, high-volume, repetitive queries (FAQ bots, customer support), the cache hit rate justifies the lookup cost. For long, unique analytical prompts, the hit rate is near zero and caching adds latency without benefit."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Portkey vs LiteLLM: Choosing Between Them"
