        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Summary"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Portkey is an LLM gateway that combines OpenAI-compatible routing with a purpose-built observability dashboard. It requires minimal code change \u2014 override the base URL and add Portkey headers \u2014 and immediately provides full request logging, latency tracking, token cost attribution, and feedback correlation. Routing features (fallback, load balancing, semantic caching) are configured as JSON objects attached per request, not server-side YAML. Choose Portkey over LiteLLM when rich LLM analytics with minimal infrastructure overhead is the priority; choose LiteLLM when full control over self-hosted key storage and YAML-configured routing is preferred."
          }
        ]
      }
